main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified aerial objects were reported by F-86 aircraft during a night training mission on 23 May 1952, and additional sightings were documented on 4 June 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as illuminated disc-shaped and observed at an altitude of approximately 25,000 feet,The sightings on 4 June 1952 included reports from airline pilots and flight crews, describing objects of varying sizes and colors,The duration of the sightings ranged from a few seconds to over 10 minutes,There was no photographic evidence or attempts to intercept the objects,The weather conditions were recorded during the sightings, indicating clear skies.
witness description: F-86 aircraft pilots and airline crew
